properties.name: isDefault
properties.description: Indicates whether this is the user's default notebook.

properties.name: userRole
properties.description: One of three values: Owner, Contributor, or Reader. Owner represents owner-level access to the notebook. Contributor represents read/write access to the notebook. Reader represents read-only access to the notebook.

properties.name: isShared
properties.description: Indicates whether the notebook is shared. If true, the contents of the notebook can be seen by people other than the owner.

properties.name: sectionsUrl
properties.description: The URL for the sections navigation property, which returns all the sections in the notebook.

properties.name: sectionGroupsUrl
properties.description: The URL for the sectionGroups navigation property, which returns all the section groups in the notebook.

properties.name: links
properties.description: The value of oneNoteClientURL can be used to open the notebook using the OneNote native client app if it's installed. The value of oneNoteWebURL can be used to open the web-browser based OneNote Online client.

properties.name: createdBy
properties.description: The user who created the notebook.

properties.name: createdByIdentity
properties.description: The user who created the notebook.

properties.name: lastModifiedBy
properties.description: The user who last modified the notebook.

properties.name: lastModifiedByIdentity
properties.description: The user who last modified the notebook.

properties.name: lastModifiedTime
properties.description: The date and time when the notebook was last modified.

properties.name: self
properties.description: The endpoint where you can get details about the notebook.

properties.name: createdTime
properties.description: The date and time when the notebook was created.
